Returns [`true`](../primitive.bool.html "primitive bool") if this is the [loopback address](about:blank/struct.Ipv6Addr.html#associatedconstant.LOCALHOST "associated constant std::net::Ipv6Addr::LOCALHOST") (`::1`), as defined in [IETF RFC 4291 section 2.5.3](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4291#section-2.5.3).

Contrary to IPv4, in IPv6 there is only one loopback address.

