Returns [`true`](../primitive.bool.html "primitive bool") if this is a unicast address, as defined by [IETF RFC 4291](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4291). Any address that is not a [multicast address](about:blank/struct.Ipv6Addr.html#method.is_multicast "method std::net::Ipv6Addr::is_multicast") (`ff00::/8`) is unicast.

##### [¬ß](#examples-12)Examples

```
#![feature(ip)]

use std::net::Ipv6Addr;

// The unspecified and loopback addresses are unicast.
assert_eq!(Ipv6Addr::UNSPECIFIED.is_unicast(), true);
assert_eq!(Ipv6Addr::LOCALHOST.is_unicast(), true);

// Any address that is not a multicast address (`ff00::/8`) is unicast.
assert_eq!(Ipv6Addr::new(0x2001, 0xdb8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).is_unicast(), true);
assert_eq!(Ipv6Addr::new(0xff00, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).is_unicast(), false);
```

